What you need to know:

There are two common physiological disorders likely to affect the tomatoes. These are Â blossom end rot and sun scalding.The calcium deficiency would be as a result of fluctuation in the watering regime or damage on the roots due to improper cultivation.It is, therefore, important to ensure the plant's roots are well taken care of during the management practices such as weeding.Sun scalding, on the other hand, occurs in areas that have high temperatures and the crop does not have proper leaf coverage.